Leicontis: Good point, which something I will rectify presently.

Agent Circeus: "a volume encompassing an area of approximately an acre." The acre is embedded is the volume that 188 acts over. Air is left unaltered, and the ground around it would have to be dug up to establish any effect, probably destroying many of the structures that 188 generates in the process. The area slice of the volume acted is the most directly observable piece of data the Foundation has. And to be technical, even the term area is a rough approximation of the slice of ground that the Foundation observes.





